addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A polynomial <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0025.xml"
addr="nt-0025"
title="Separable Polynomial">separable</fr:link> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p'(x)]]></fr:tex> have no common root.</fr:p><fr:p>Note: by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p'(x)]]></fr:tex> we mean the formal derivative. That is, if
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[p(x)=a_{n}x^{n}+a_{n-1}x^{n-1}+…+a_{1}x+a_{0},]]></fr:tex>
then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[p'(x)=na_{n}x^{n-1}+(n-1)a_{n-1}x^{n-2}+…+a_{1}.]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
 
   
